4 HACKS which will MASK PROOF 😷 your Lipstick💄✨😉

✨1. Get rid of excess lip balm from your lips. It’s good to hydrate and moisturise the lips before lipstick application but having it under your lipstick can make the lipstick slip and slide on the mask. 
So apply your lip balm while you do your makeup and once it’s time to do your lips just take cotton and wipe it off. 

✨2. Always use a lip liner. It will give your lipstick a smooth canvas to stick to, generally lipliners are water, smudge and transfer proof which will make sure your lipstick stays put under that mask. 

✨3. Avoid creamy and satin finish lipsticks, and switch to matte lipsticks. I know glosses and creamy lipsticks are in trend but they are a big no no when wearing a face mask. 

✨4. Set the lipstick. Once you have applied the lip colour, place a tissue over your lips , take some translucent powder and dab it on the paper. Dust off the excess and gently remove the tissue. The powder will absorb the excess colour and moisture and set the lips. 

❤️Hope these hacks help you, if they do don’t forget to like and share this video with someone who might need it this festive season!
